{"lemma":"شاة","slug":"شاة","root":"ش.#.ه","root_slug":"ش-_-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23250","n23394","n23413"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a sheep","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a ewe, a female sheep","tags":["singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Found under the root ش و ه (š w h) in Lane (see below), and in a cross-reference under the same root in Wehr (see below). Compare Hebrew שֶׂה (śe, “lamb”), Ugaritic 𐎘𐎀𐎚 (ṯảt)."},"ipa":["/ʃaːh/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23250","headword_ar":"شَاهٍ","root":"$hw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Desiring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"longing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Sb, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhiY AlbaSari","text_ar":"شَاهِى البَصَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp of sight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAy^ihu AlbaSari","text_ar":"شَايِهُ البَصَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n23394","headword_ar":"شَاةٌ","root":"$wh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhapN","text_ar":"شَاهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but more commonly the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"former;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an instance voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwfN","text_ar":"صُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganam","text_ar":"غَنَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * Msb, * K;) applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) so that one says of the male,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA $aApN","text_ar":"هٰذَا شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) which is said by Kh to be like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA raHomapN mino rab~iY","text_ar":"هٰذَا رَحْمَةٌ مِنْ رَبِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, TA;) and of the female,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi $aApN","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN *akarN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN A^unovaY","text_ar":"شَاةٌ اُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it may be ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gazelles"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"antelopes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bovine kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the wild bovine kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of bovine antelopes"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of ostriches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wild asses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wild bull"},{"kind":"text","text":"by Tarafeh, in his saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kasaAmiEataYo $aApK biHawomala muforadi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the two ears of a wild bull, in Howmal, solitary;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poet likening thereto the ears of a she-camel in respect of sharpness and erectness; (EM p. 76;) and likewise by Lebeed, and by El-Farezdak: (IB, TA:) and it is also applied to ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wild cow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(though said in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wY","text_ar":"شوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild bull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"specially the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male;"},{"kind":"text","text":") and hence, as being likened thereto,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) thus by El-Aashà; and thus also by Antarah, in his saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA $aApa maA qanaSK limano Hal~ato lahu\n                      \n                     \n                        Harumato EalaY~a walayotahaA lamo taHorumi"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1624},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Ap","text_ar":"شاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild cow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the chase"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"being redundant)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for him to whom she is lawful: she has become forbidden to me, and would that she were not forbidden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(EM p. 246:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA='N","text_ar":"شَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhN","text_ar":"شَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) used when they are many in number, (S,) [but this is properly termed a coll. gen. n.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyaAhN","text_ar":"شِيَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is used of a number from three to ten [inclusive], for more than which it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with a general rule], (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iwaAhN","text_ar":"شِوَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the original of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyaAhN","text_ar":"شِيَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awiY~N","text_ar":"شَوِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awFY","text_ar":"شَوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA='N","text_ar":"شَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or rather a quasi-pl. n., originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awiyhN","text_ar":"شَوِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iY","text_ar":"ذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iho","text_ar":"ذِهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAwihu","text_ar":"اَشَاوِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayohN","text_ar":"شَيْهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in copies of the K, [in the TA said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinabN","text_ar":"عِنَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mistake, (perhaps for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) for it is there said to be a quasi-pl. n., which could not be said if it were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyahN","text_ar":"شِيَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyhN","text_ar":"شِيهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (CK, [but this, which is another quasi-pl. n., is not in my MS. copy of the K nor in the TA,]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~ihN","text_ar":"شَيِّهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayowihN","text_ar":"شَيْوِهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this, also, is a quasi-pl. n., (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyapN","text_ar":"شِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA='N","text_ar":"شَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wY","text_ar":"شوى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it has not a pl. formed with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. it has not for a pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAA=tN","text_ar":"شَاا=تٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] whether it be used as a gen. n. or as a proper name: (TA:) the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uwayohapN","text_ar":"شُوَيْهَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) The sing. is also used in the sense of the pl., in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN kaviyru Al$~aApi waAlbaEiyri","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ كَثِيرُ الشَّاةِ وَالبَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is possessor of a large number of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, and of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes the genus. (S.) And it is said in a trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^amara lahaA bi$iyaAhi ganamK","text_ar":"فَاَمَرَ لَهَا بِشِيَاهِ غَنَمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he ordered that sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats should be given to her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$yAh","text_ar":"شياه"},{"kind":"text","text":"being prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gnm","text_ar":"غنم"},{"kind":"text","text":", governing it in the gen. case, for the sake of distinction; because the Arabs [sometimes] call an animal of the wild bovine kind"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Ap","text_ar":"شاة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aApu","text_ar":"الشَّاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain small stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wY","text_ar":"شوى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqrHh","text_ar":"القرحه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfrjp","text_ar":"الفرجة"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus in the work of Kzw, in his descr. of Cepheus, and there said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star in the breast of Cepheus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljadoYu","text_ar":"الجَدْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pole-star"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA in that art.;) [the same that are described by Kzw as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain small stars, called by the Arabs"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^agonaAmu","text_ar":"الاَغْنَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the legs of Cepheus and the star"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljadoYu","text_ar":"الجَدْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","IB","K","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n23413","headword_ar":"شَاةٌ","root":"$wY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows: and see more in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wh","text_ar":"شوه"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":1625}],"source_refs":[]}]}}